        ## Getting Started
        
        ## Examples
        ```python
        from bpipe import *
        
        for r in echo("Hello World") | map_to(lambda x: x.upper()):
            print(r)
        
        # HELLO WORLD
        ```
        
        ### Installation
        
        Just install it with the pip client:
        
        ```bash
        pip install bpipe
        ```
        
        Or from source code:
        
        ```python
        git clone https://github.com/jepemo/basic-pipeline
        cd basic-pipeline
        python3 -m venv venv
        source venv/bin/activate
        pip install -e .
        ```
        
        ### Tests
        ```python
        python setup.py test
        ```
        
